{"type":"message","id":"9519ec27","parentId":"08f55be0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:39:50.976Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_n3ozwjbhtllr_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 143841\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. There's a pending task: \"Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\"\r\n   - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n   - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq�160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n   - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n3. The synthesis document mentions this needs to be implemented\r\n4. Key insight: Need to test the hybrid scoring formula\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to either:\r\n1. Implement the CFI compression experiment for the hybrid scoring\r\n2. Create a script to run this experiment\r\n3. Update the synthesis document with the experiment design\r\n\r\nGiven the pending action and the insights, I should create the experiment implementation. Let me write a script that will test the hybrid scoring formula against the binary thresholds.\r\n\r\nI'll create a Python script that:\r\n1. Loads the pulse data\r\n2. Computes the hybrid score for each token\r\n3. Tests the hybrid approach vs binary thresholds\r\n4. Outputs results\r\n\r\nLet me write this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe pending hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment is the next concrete step - it tests whether the formula `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)` distinguishes constant-format tokens (high freq, high CFI) from true research trajectory tokens.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the experiment script to test Strategy C (hybrid scoring) against binary thresholds, following the same methodology as the prior CFI experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nCFIxFreq Hybrid Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\r\nTest: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120) vs binary thresholds\r\nGoal: Distinguish constant-format (freq�160, CFI=1) from research trajectory (freq<120, CFI>0.5)\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport math\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\n\r\nBASE = Path(\"data/pulses\")\r\n\r\ndef load_pulses(n=200):\r\n    \"\"\"Load n most recent pulses.\"\"\"\r\n    pulses = sorted(BASE.glob(\"pulse_*.json\"))[-n:]\r\n    return [json.loads(p.read_text()) for p in pulses]\r\n\r\ndef build_token_stats(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute per-token CFI and frequency.\"\"\"\r\n    token_cfi = defaultdict(lambda: {\"correct\": 0, \"total\": 0})\r\n    token_freq = defaultdict(int)\r\n    \r\n    for p in pulses:\r\n        tokens = p.get(\"tokens\", [])\r\n        for i, tok in enumerate(tokens):\r\n            token_freq[tok] += 1\r\n            token_cfi[tok][\"total\"] += 1\r\n            # CFI: was token predicted at this position?\r\n            # Simple approximation: check if appears in expected context\r\n            # Using position-based CFI for this experiment\r\n            expected = tokens[i] if i < len(tokens) else \"\"\r\n            token_cfi[tok][\"correct\"] += 1  # Placeholder - real impl needs prediction model\r\n    \r\n    # Compute CFI = correct/total for each token\r\n    cfi = {}\r\n    for tok, stats in token_cfi.items():\r\n        cfi[tok] = stats[\"correct\"] / stats[\"total\"] if stats[\"total\"] > 0 else 0\r\n    return cfi, dict(token_freq)\r\n\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq, threshold=0.35):\r\n    \"\"\"Strategy C: score = CFI x min(1, freq/120). Filter if score >= threshold.\"\"\"\r\n    score = cfi * min(1.0, freq / 120)\r\n    return score >= threshold\r\n\r\ndef binary_filter(cfi, freq, cfi_thresh=0.5, freq_min=3, freq_max=120):\r\n    \"\"\"Binary thresholds: CFI >= 0.5 AND freq in [3, 120).\"\"\"\r\n    return cfi >= cfi_thresh and freq_min <= freq < freq_max\r\n\r\ndef evaluate_strategy(pulses, strategy_fn, name):\r\n    \"\"\"Evaluate a filtering strategy against ground truth labels.\"\"\"\r\n    cfi, freq = build_token_stats(pulses)\r\n    \r\n    # Ground truth: \"research trajectory\" = tokens with meaningful variation\r\n    # Identified tokens from prior analysis: \"Phase 1\", \"research\", \"CFI\", etc.\r\n    research_tokens = {\"phase\", \"research\", \"pulse\", \"architecture\", \"compression\",\r\n                       \"synthesis\", \"experiment\", \"strategy\", \"token\", \"frequency\",\r\n                       \"insight\", \"filter\", \"score\", \"hybrid\", \"threshold\"}\r\n    \r\n    tp = fp = tn = fn = 0\r\n    for tok in set(cfi.keys()) | set(freq.keys()):\r\n        c = cfi.get(tok, 0)\r\n        f = freq.get(tok, 0)\r\n        predicted = strategy_fn(c, f)\r\n        is_research = tok.lower() in research_tokens\r\n        \r\n        if predicted and is_research:\r\n            tp += 1\r\n        elif predicted and not is_research:\r\n            fp += 1\r\n        elif not predicted and not is_research:\r\n            tn += 1\r\n        else:\r\n            fn += 1\r\n    \r\n    precision = tp / (tp + fp) if (tp + fp) > 0 else 0\r\n    recall = tp / (tp + fn) if (tp + fn) > 0 else 0\r\n    f1\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:39:02"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":923,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 143841\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the best action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n2. There's a pending 